1464	\section{A universal field-size cap via list-to-agreement conversion}\label{sec:cap}
1465	
1466	The imported Crites--Stewart conversion states that correlated agreement with sufficiently small error forces small list sizes \cite{CS25}; the survey \cite{ABF26} records this as the basic conversion between the two grand challenges.  Composing the contrapositive with the quotient-core lists of \cref{thm:qcore} conditionally caps the achievable mutual-correlated-agreement threshold over \emph{every} field of challenge size, prime or extension, with no value-set counting at all.  Throughout, $\eca(C,\delta)$ denotes the correlated-agreement error in the normalization of \cref{def:mca}: the maximal density of parameters $z$ for which $f+zg$ is $\delta$-close to $C$ while no common agreement set of density $1-\delta$ explains $f$ and $g$ simultaneously.  Every such $z$ is in particular support-wise MCA-bad, so
1467	\begin{equation}\label{eq:camca}
1468	        \emca(C,\delta)\ \ge\ \eca(C,\delta).
1469	\end{equation}
1470	
1471	\begin{theorem}[Imported: list-to-agreement conversion; \cite{CS25}, Theorem~2, as restated in \cite{ABF26}]\label{thm:capimport}
1472	Let $C=\RS[\F_q,D,k]$ with $|D|=n$, and let $\delta\in(0,1-\rho]$.  If
1473	\[
1474	        \eca(C,\delta)\ \le\ \eta\left(\frac1k-\frac n{kq}\right)
1475	        \qquad\text{for some }\eta\in(0,1),
1476	\]
1477	then the $\delta$-list size of the relevant augmented code $C^+\supseteq C$ satisfies $\Lst(C^+,\delta)\le\lceil q\,\eca(C,\delta)/(1-\eta)\rceil$.  We use only the consequence $\Lst(C,\delta)\le\Lst(C^+,\delta)$; see \cref{rem:diligence} for the bookkeeping this import requires.
1478	\end{theorem}
